thread.title: New Zealand Opposition Leader Bill English to Retire

author: Ben Collins
title: New Zealand Opposition Leader Bill English to Retire
text:
WELLINGTON, New Zealand—Bill English, the former prime minister and leader of New Zealand’s center-right National Party will step down later this month. 
Mr. English, also a former finance minister, led National to an election in September last year that eventually ended the party’s nearly decadelong incumbency.
